issue.title: doc/Makefile fails if path contains spaces - Fixes #65623
issue.body:
This pull request fixes #65623

The python script failed to find the path as the space made the makefile think that it was another argument.

With this pull request there can be spaces included in the path of where the godot repo is saved.

comment.body:
> I struggled with this for a while yesterday, but before I went to bed, I realized that the solution is probably this:
> 
> ```diff
> diff --git a/doc/Makefile b/doc/Makefile
> index ecc5e51dd6..c8bf32d6e2 100644
> --- a/doc/Makefile
> +++ b/doc/Makefile
> @@ -1,4 +1,4 @@
> -BASEDIR = $(CURDIR)
> +BASEDIR = .
>  CLASSES = $(BASEDIR)/classes/ $(BASEDIR)/../modules/
>  OUTPUTDIR = $(BASEDIR)/_build
>  TOOLSDIR = $(BASEDIR)/tools
> ```
> 
> But, I haven‚Äôt tested it yet.

Just tested it and works fine, committed the change.
